---
description: Marketing site conventions — design taste layer
globs: src/app/(marketing)/**
---

- One idea per section. One primary CTA per page. Sections use py-24 md:py-32.
- Typography carries the design: max 2 typefaces, large confident headings
  (hero: clamp-based, tight tracking, text-balance), generous body leading.
- Copy voice: verbs, outcomes, numbers. Banned words: revolutionize, unleash,
  supercharge, empower, seamless.
- Motion: animate opacity/transform only; 0.3–0.6s ease-out; stagger 60–100ms;
  everything respects prefers-reduced-motion; no looping animation in the
  initial viewport except deliberate ambient elements.
- Use motion (Framer Motion) for reveals; GSAP + ScrollTrigger only for
  dedicated scroll scenes; lazy-load heavy scenes below the fold.
- Real product screenshots in framed mocks over abstract illustrations.
- Performance budget: Lighthouse ≥ 95, LCP < 2s, CLS = 0. Hero image priority.
- All brand strings/links from config/brand.ts; colors from tokens only.
- After building/changing a section, verify with a browser screenshot at
  390 / 768 / 1440 px against the section spec before marking done.
